    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - REASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="9">
            <title>MAINSHAFT REASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lube all bearings before beginning reassembly. Continue by placing the caged needle
                    bearing and 1st speed gear (hub toward clutch gear) on the shaft. Position the thrust washer on the
                    shaft, then press the bearing race into place,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300663">Figure 63</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300663" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300663" filename="../figg13/g1300663.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 63. Lube All Bearings</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the mainshaft in a vise with protected jaws or in a holding fixture,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300664">Figure 64</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300664" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300664" filename="../figg13/g1300664.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 64. Mainshaft in Vise</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide 1st/2nd speed synchronizer on the shaft. Shift it into gear,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300665">Figure 65</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300665" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300665" filename="../figg13/g1300665.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 65. 1st/2nd Speed Synchronizer</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the caged needle bearing and 2nd speed gear onto the shaft. The gear hub should
                    point toward 1st/2nd speed synchronizer. Position the lock ball into the shaft and slide the thrust
                    washer into place. The lock ball keeps the thrust washer from rotating on the shaft. Install snap
                    ring with rounded side toward thrust washer,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300666">Figure 66</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300666" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300666" filename="../figg13/g1300666.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 66. Install Snap Ring</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position two caged needle bearings (wider one first) on the shaft. Slide 3rd speed gear
                    on the shaft with the clutching teeth up. Also install 3rd/4th speed clutch gear. Secure it with a
                    snap ring. The rounded side of the snap ring should face the clutch gear,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300667">Figure 67</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300667" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300667" filename="../figg13/g1300667.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 67. Install 3rd/4th Speed Clutch Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the 3rd/4th speed synchronizer,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300668">Figure 68</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300668" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300668" filename="../figg13/g1300668.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 68. 3rd/4th Speed Synchronizer</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Next, install the two caged needle bearings and 4th speed gear. The gear hub should face
                    the synchronizer. Put the lock ball into place. Then install the thrust washer and snap ring,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300669">Figure 69</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300669" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300669" filename="../figg13/g1300669.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 69. 4th Speed Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two caged needle bearings and either the overdrive gear (for the overdrive
                    version) or the 5th speed gear (for the direct version). The clutch teeth should face up. Install
                    the 5th/6th speed clutch gear, and secure it with the snap ring,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300670">Figure 70</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300670" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300670" filename="../figg13/g1300670.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 70. 5th Speed Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press the drive gear pocket bearing onto the end of the shaft. The chamfered side of the
                    bearing should face the 5th/6th speed clutch gear,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300671">Figure 71</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300671" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300671" filename="../figg13/g1300671.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 71. Drive Gear Pocket Bearing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
